==Eras of Sanetomo's ''bakufu''==
The years in which Sanetomo was shogun are more specifically identified by more than one [[:en:Japanese era names|era name]] or ''[[:en:Nengō|Nengō]]''.
* ''{{ill|Kennin|en|Kennin|qid=Q1195433|lt=Kennin|1=Kennin}}'' (1201–1204)
* ''{{ill|Genkyū|en|Genkyū|qid=Q1194276|lt=Genkyū|1=Genkyū}}'' (1204–1206)
* ''{{ill|Ken'ei|en|Ken'ei|qid=Q1194153|lt=Ken'ei|1=Ken'ei}}'' (1206–1207)
* ''{{ill|Jōgen (Kamakura period)|en|Jōgen (Kamakura period)|qid=Q1194389|lt=Jōgen (Kamakura period)|1=Jōgen (Kamakura period)}}'' (1207–1211)
* ''{{ill|Kenryaku|en|Kenryaku|qid=Q1194260|lt=Kenryaku|1=Kenryaku}}'' (1211–1213)
* ''{{ill|Kempo (era)|en|Kempo (era)|qid=Q1194251|lt=Kenpō|1=Kempo (era)}}'' (1213–1219)
* ''{{ill|Jōkyū|en|Jōkyū|qid=Q1195428|lt=Jōkyū|1=Jōkyū}}'' (1219–1222)

